It seems the message is clear: men should give up control of the wine list, as they are twice as fearful of getting it wrong. 

Choosing wine is one of the things that makes Britons most anxious – and men are far more uneasy about it than women.

One in eight (11.5 per cent) men say what makes them most uncomfortable - even more than spiders - is choosing wine in a restaurant or to go with food at a party.

