Job interviews rank top for both women (28.5 per cent) and men (24.5 per cent). 

And, in a less formal context, both sexes hate being at a social occasion where they don't know anyone – 25 per cent of women and 22 per cent of men rank this as the situation that makes them most uncomfortable. 

The research was commissioned by an online wine specialist Naked Wine who surveyed 2,000 people to uncover how scared Brits were of ordering wine. 

Eamon FitzGerald Managing Director of Naked Wines said: 'As a social business we love delving in to what makes our  the public tick. It's unusual our survey showed that men find ordering wine more scary than spiders - but we aim to take the fear out of ordering wine and make it an enjoyable experience for customers.'

